Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Halve, peel
and thinly slice the @red onion{1/2}. Thinly slice the @chestnut mushrooms{150%g}
and @portobello mushrooms{2}. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(grated) (or
use a #garlic press{}). Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%sprig}(finely chopped,
stalks and all). Pour half the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} into a #bowl{}, add the
@olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix
together and leave to the side.

When boiling, add the @penne pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the
boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. When the pasta is cooked, drain in a
#colander{} and pop back into the #pan{}. Drizzle with a little @olive oil{} and
stir through to stop it sticking together. Set aside off the heat.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} on
medium heat. Add the mushrooms and cook until browned, stirring occasionally,
~{6-7%minutes}. Once browned, reduce the heat to medium-low and add the
onion. Cook, stirring frequently until the onion is soft, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add
the garlic and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir and cook for
~{1%minute}. Add the remaining balsamic vinegar, stir and cook until evaporated,
~{1%minute}.

> Step 3 MOD: If you've opted to get bacon added to your meal, add the
@?bacon lardons{90%g} to your pan before you add the mushrooms and cook for
~{2%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw
meat. Then add the mushrooms and continue with the rest of the recipe as
instructed.

Pour the @water{150%ml} for the sauce into your frying pan and stir in the
@vegetable stock paste{10%g}. Increase the heat and bring to the boil, then
reduce the heat to low and simmer until reduced, ~{5-6%minutes}, stirring
occasionally. Stir in the @creme fraiche{99%g} until well combined, bring
back to the boil and add a good grind of @ground black pepper{}. Remove from
the heat.

Add the cooked pasta to the sauce along with three quarters of the
@grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and three quarters of the parsley.
Stir everything together. Taste and add more @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Spoon your pasta into #bowls{} and sprinkle the remaining cheese and parsley
on top. Add the @wild rocket{40%g} to the balsamic dressing and toss together.
Serve on top of the pasta and finish with a good grind of black pepper. Enjoy!